main event: Multiple witnesses observed unidentified objects in the sky over Stockton, California on March 3 and 6, 1959.
interesting points: One sighting involved a white circular object that lasted about five minutes with no noise or condensation trail,Other witnesses included USAF pilots who saw a bright reddish object at high altitude,The object was not identified by any known aircraft and was not detected on radar,Housewives reported multiple fast-moving silver-white objects that appeared and disappeared during the observation,The report classifies the sightings as UNIDENTIFIED due to the unusual characteristics of the objects.
